 3. Core Architectural Layers

---

3.1 User Layer

Actors:

- Pioneers
- Merchants
- Developers

Role:

- Generate economic activity
- Provide real-world utility

---

3.2 Application Layer

Components:

- Marketplace
- Freelance platforms
- Games
- DeFi applications

---

Function:

«Converts user actions into measurable economic signals»

---

3.3 Data & Signal Layer

Inputs:

- Transactions
- User behavior
- Engagement metrics

---

Output:

Structured signals for PiRC processing

---

«This layer transforms raw activity into economic data»

---

3.4 PiRC Economic Layer (CORE)

This is the brain of the system

---

 WCF Engine (Weighted Contribution Factor)

- Scores:
  - Contribution quality
  - Activity value
  - Long-term participation

---

 Φ Engine (System Efficiency Factor)

- Monitors:
  - Liquidity health
  - Market stability
  - System stress

---

 Reward Engine ($REF)

- Allocates:
  - Incentives
  - Contribution rewards

---

 Policy Engine

- Adjusts:
  - Reward curves
  - Liquidity parameters
  - System thresholds

---

«Together, these modules create a closed-loop economic system»

---

3.5 Execution Layer

Technologies:

- Stellar Soroban (primary target)
- EVM-compatible chains (secondary)

---

Role:

- Enforce economic rules
- Execute reward distribution
- Manage liquidity contracts

---

3.6 Settlement Layer

Function:

- Finalize transactions
- Maintain ledger integrity

---

«This layer ensures trust and immutability»

---

 4. Data Flow Pipeline

User Action
   ↓
App Interaction
   ↓
Data Capture (API / Oracle)
   ↓
PiRC Processing (WCF + Φ)
   ↓
Reward Allocation ($REF)
   ↓
Smart Contract Execution
   ↓
Blockchain Settlement
   ↓
Feedback to User

---

 5. Cross-Layer Interaction

Upward Flow:

- Value creation → economic scoring → reward

Downward Flow:

- Policy decisions → contract execution → user incentives

---

«PiRC acts as a bidirectional coordination layer»

---

 6. Modular Design

Each component is independently upgradeable:

- WCF Engine → scoring logic upgrade
- Φ Engine → new stability models
- Reward Engine → new incentive mechanisms
- Policy Engine → AI integration

---

«Enables continuous evolution without system disruption»

---

 7. AI Integration Layer (Advanced)

PiRC integrates AI for:

- Behavior prediction
- Economic simulation
- Adaptive policy tuning

---

Capabilities:

- Detect anomalies
- Optimize reward distribution
- Prevent systemic risk

---

«The system becomes predictive, not reactive»

---

 8. Security Architecture

Multi-Layer Defense:

Layer 1 — Behavioral

- WCF anomaly detection

Layer 2 — Economic

- Φ-based stabilization

Layer 3 — Protocol

- Smart contract enforcement

Layer 4 — Data

- Oracle validation

---

«No single point of failure»

---

 9. External Interface Layer

PiRC connects to:

- Exchanges (IOU markets)
- External liquidity providers
- Cross-chain bridges

---

Model:

Internal Economy (Macro Pi)
        ↓
Bridge Layer
        ↓
External Markets (Micro Pi)

---

«External markets influence, but do not control, internal value»

---

